# .mailmap — canonicalize commit-identity DISPLAY to a single identity.
#
# This is a DISPLAY-LAYER map only. It normalizes how git CLI tooling
# (git log, blame, shortlog, and anything that honors mailmap) shows author
# and committer identities. It does NOT rewrite commit objects, does NOT change
# any commit SHA, and does NOT alter Signed-off-by trailers in commit messages.
#
# All of the identities below are Greg Chism (project founder). They accumulated
# from an institutional email, a GitHub web-UI author identity, and the canonical
# project email. Each maps to the single canonical identity:
#
#     Greg Chism <greg@steppe.community>
#
# Not mapped: `GitHub <noreply@github.com>` — that is GitHub's own committer
# identity on the two web-UI "Initial commit" commits, not a personal identity,
# so it is deliberately left untouched.

Greg Chism <greg@steppe.community> <gchism@arizona.edu>
Greg Chism <greg@steppe.community> Greg T. Chism <38962243+Gchism94@users.noreply.github.com>
